  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Facilitation of Cross Border Operations from Turkey to Syria and Logistics Support for the Humanitarian Actors</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Turkish Red Crescent has been providing border facilitation since 2012 for the logistics of the cross border operations of all humanitarian actors, particularly the NGOs, responding from Turkey to Syria Crisis. This facilitation mainly includes enabling import and export with waivers, exemption from the Value Added Tax (VAT) for the humanitarian supplies, fast track at the border crossings, use of additional border crossings (humanitarian aidl border crossings, those without a customs office such as Atmeh) through most direct routes, coordination of cross border shipments to avoid congestion and allow expedited access and information sharing. The project aims to enhance and strengthen the capacity of the TRC, throughout the project duration, to provide these services to the humanitarian community by deploying required amount of human resources and logistics services, providing warehouse and transportation facility for the humanitarian actors, building the capacity of the TRC and NGO staff members to ensure that the cross border operations continue uninterruptedly that directly impacts the humanitarian reach inside Syria. TRC is providing humanitarian aid crossings in 5 cities ( Gaziantep, Kilis, Hatay, &#x15E;anl&#x131;urfa, Mardin) from 12 border points. TRC has offices and staffs in these cities and border crossing points</narrative>
  </description>
